article.headline: Tenn.-Martin 63, Murray St. 38
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. -- Cade Thompson threw for 250 yards and four touchdowns to lead Tennessee-Martin to a 63-38 victory against Murray State on Saturday night. Roren Thomas also scored four touchdowns, including an 83-yard kick return touchdown, and compiled 223 total yards for the Skyhawks (4-1, 2-0 Ohio Valley Conference). Jeff Ehrhardt completed 25 of 43 passes for 375 yards with four touchdowns and two interceptions, and also added 51 yards on 11 carries for the Racers (1-4, 0-1). Thomas opened the scoring with his kickoff return on the game's first play, and Thompson hooked up with Thomas on a 12-yard pass three minutes later to put the Skyhawks ahead 14-0. Still in the first, Ehrhardt and Daniel Ard connected on a 6-yard pass to pull the Racers within a touchdown. But Tennessee-Martin's Dontrell Miller scored on a 10-yard interception return and a 32-yard fumble return to close the opening quarter with a 28-7 lead. The teams scored twice each in the second, including Brandyn Young's 6-yard rushing score and Thomas' 20-yard run that put the Skyhawks up 42-17 at the half. Thompson connected on touchdown passes of 45 and 29 yards in the third for the Skyhawks. Ehrhardt hit on 47- and 13-yard scores of his own in the same quarter with the Racers trailing 56-31. But Thompson threw another touchdown pass at the start of the fourth quarter that put the Skyhawks ahead 63-31, and a late Murray State touchdown would not be enough. Murray State's Derrick Townsell caught nine passes for 161 yards and a touchdown in the loss.
